This paper proposes a deep learning-based colorfulness estimation metric for natural images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could potentially fall under machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a subjective test, which could potentially fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, but since the focus is on the technical aspect of the colorfulness estimation metric, it is less likely. Finally, the paper involves the use of datasets and quantitative evaluation, which could potentially fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
